29/03/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UN police on Tuesday (28 March) closed a bridge linking the ethnic Albanian and Serb quarters of the divided city of Mitrovica, after hundreds of Serbs gathered to protest the stabbing of a teenager Monday evening.
The 19-year-old Serb is in serious condition at hospital.
Police could not confirm that the attackers were ethnic Albanians.
The stabbing occurred on the bridge.
(Politika - 29/03/06;
Reuters, RTS - 28/03/06)
